name: Perimeter Screen Pre-Climb Checklist
General Items
Ensure all façade trades are clear of screens
Ensure no loose items left within 2.0 mtr of screens
All areas including top working deck and ground floor below screens, have been bunted off and signage installed prior to screen climbing. (Ground floor exclusion zone to be 10 mtr)
Ensure bunting is in place & spotters on each level during the screen climbing process. Spotters to each have radio contact.
Traffic controllers are aware that screen climbing is in process and traffic is stopped during vertical movement (as applicable)
Individual Screen Items
Screen working and catch decks are clear of all debris and rubbish
All screen needles and equipment are installed on the newly poured floor.
All screen needles and equipment are removed from the redundant floor, and stacked away from the edge of structure
Scaffolding and formwork materials have been checked to ensure no clashing or catching during climbing, including mesh infill strips.
All flaps, gap covers and restraints are folded back or removed and secured
Façade is complete OR approved edge protection is in place on lowest floor prior to climb.
Remove pins at prop to needle connections. Collapse props and fold in to hang position between soldier channels ensuring prop inner to outer connecting pins are in position and locking R-clips fitted
Near Hoist installations
Communicate with hoist operator to park hoist on lowest floor until climbing of adjoining screen is complete and screen is released by crane.
Formwork
Check Structural members for suitability
Check suitability of forms and linings having regard to class
Check false work
As per the shop drawings
Adequate bracing to verticals
Sole plates for material, size, position
Pins inserted in props where required
Members bearing fully on support
Wedges in place
Verticality of props and alignment with props below
Obtain approval of class 3 in line with AS3610.
Check plan set out using steel tape to verify accuracy in positions of edge form, walls and columns
Check levels with due allowance for approved combers using optical or laser levels
Check vertical forms for verticality alignment and squareness of corners
Check forms thoroughly for cleanliness and surface suitability
Check exposed edges for size, position & straightness as shown on drawings for 20 x 20 chamfers and drip grooves etc.
Check the inserts, penetration, bolts and cast ins shown on drawings. Check location of joints and application of release agents
Formwork Engineer to inspect the formwork deck and issue certificate
Check deflection and movement of formwork during concreting operations
Close off area, allowing formworkers only beyond this point during formwork erection and maintain during concrete pour using bunting and signage

No materials protruding through wall or door openings

Structural steel door beam tilt foot support column installed
All other trades are removed from system prior to climbing
Communication in place with site office

Scaffolders on standby to erect temporary scaffold to access stair

Pre Pour
Check that all tie rods are tight
Internal and External shutters need to be plumb and straight
Ensure overall dimension are correct as per drawings
Ensure all peno's have been installed
Spacers installed to tops of columns where needed
Tightness of corners to be checked twice
Ensure that the required class of finish will be met
Check all fillets and drip grooves
Check all cast-ins and bolts
Check joints, fillets and application of release agents
Checklist to be used in conjunction with ITP
Jumpform Handover
Has builder received formworkers ‘PERMIT TO RE-SEAT’ Checklist
All tie bolts removed & stored
All rolling shutters retracted
All fixed shutters fully struck
All steel corners full struck
All penetrations meshed
All rubbish removed & storage bins
All loose material secured stored
Escape routes identified & clear
External trailing deck swept clear of debris
TWP timber planks to be properly secured using screws & handrails in place
No load zones clear & free from load
Jacking deck edge flaps closed
Jacking deck extendable ladders in position
Access hatch covers /gates fitted & functioning correctly
Temporary access ladders secured at top & bottom
Gaps between core walls & decks are sealed
Penetration covers installed & secured
Fall protection in place to all leading edges
General housekeeping - Work areas tidy & free from obstacles, debris etc.
Sufficient access to work areas
Stripping In Situ Slab
Written Approval is to be given by the builder
Notify builder when stripping will commence and ensure scaffolder progressively follows
Physical barriers and signage to be installed above and below the slab that is being striped
Builder to install permanent handrails around large penos and live edges with no scaffold
Above the deck, clean off any debris from the cantilevered section of deck
Designate areas where material is to be stacked and can be accessed by pallet jack etc.
Ensure skip bins are empty and easily accessible for disposal of off cuts, nails, rubbish etc.
Securely install planks to frames, multiple layers if exceeding one frame high
Follow SWMS 010 which refers to safe stripping of formwork decks
Whilst stacking material, ensure denailing of all material
Plywood sheets, edge boards and Timbers/Bearer to be stacked according to size
Stacked Plywood sheets must have sides scraped clean and square
All material must be strapped without overtightening
Ensure that the striped slab has backpropping reinstated in accordance with the drawing
Formwork Certificate:
Ensure that scaffolder has installed all hop ups and other scaffolding required
Once scaffold is in place and area is swept clean remove barriers and signage
Perimeter Screen Post-Climb Checklist
Screens installed as per engineer specifications
All clips and connectors secure and tight
Perimeter screen continuous – Minimal gaps
Catch decks in good order – cover plates and flaps against structure, kickboards and purlin rubbers – NO GAPS
Working decks in good order – cover plates and flaps against structure, kick boards and purlin rubbers (as applicable)
Leading deck formwork flaps secure and minimal gaps
Clear safe access provided to working decks
Edge protection secure over needles and boxed in (as applicable)
Mesh infills / scaffold integrations secure
Loading within specified rating 220 kg max.

Check builders drawing register to ensure working off latest drawings
Read plans and discuss any problem areas
Add delivery times to the crane board

Check beam / soffit step, set down and Hob locations shown on drawings
Check for drawings for cast ins, bolts, joints and Filets
Check that all release agents have been used
Erect formwork to AS3610 requirements
Erect catch decks if required and as per SWMS
Erect handrail progressively as deck is built
Mark edge boards from survey
